article.headline: Cent. Michigan 71, W. Michigan 68
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- Robbie Harman put Central Michigan ahead to stay with his fourth 3-pointer of the game with 1:53 to go, and the Chippewas defeated Western Michigan 71-68 Sunday. Central, Western and Ball State share the Mid-American Conference West Division title despite sub-.500 records (7-9) in league play. The Broncos (10-20 overall) led by as many as 14 points, 46-32, on Martelle McLemore's jumper with 12:14 remaining. The Chippewas (11-18) responded with a 26-13 run over the next 9 minutes to move within 59-58, and led the rest of the way after Harman's trey. Jordan Bitzer scored 19 points, Marcus Van had 16 points and 13 rebounds and Harman finished with 12 points for Central. Western's David Kool scored a game-high 21 points and Andre Ricks had 15.
